  "text": "I need my beauty rest! Hummingbird CLOSE YOUR EYES When darkness falls, you finally stop moving! On chilly nights. you go into a deep sleep called torpor. Torpor can last between five and ten hours. Torpor is similar to hibernation-it helps you survive cold temperatures. Unlike humans. you need to constantly refill your energy when you're awake. Torpor slows your metabolism. the process that turns food into energy. this lets you go a long time without eating. Your heart rate can slow to as few as SO beats per minute while you sleep. During the day. it can reach beats per minute. You like to on a tree branch where you feel safe from predators. It you lay eggs. youll sleep in your nest (More about nests on the next page!) Sometimes you sleep upside down! the first thing you do after you wake from torpor? Eat. of course'",
